---
title: Pork, Eggplant, and Squash Stir-Fry with Sesame and Ginger over Brown Rice
description: We love the way eggplant with garlic sauce revels in contrasts, placing equal emphasis on the sweet, the sour, and the savory. But when we wanted to do it the HelloFresh way, we decided to make it bigger and bolder, adding in hearty ground pork and slices of bright yellow squash. The end result is something that feels satisfying and wholesome, especially on top of a bed of hearty brown rice.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/w21-r4-0ee6b28a.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/w21-r4-26d86e63.pdf
nutrition:
  calories: 710 kcal
  fat: 35 g
  saturated fat: 8 g
  carbohydrates: 74 g
  sugar: 8 g
  protein: 30 g
  fiber: 9 g
  sodium: 370 mg
cuisine: Asian
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/pork-eggplant-and-squash-stir-fry-58e6624151d3f1524a0c3e82
servings: 2
author: HelloFresh
course: main course
time required: 35 minutes
---

Bring a medium #pot{} of salted water to a boil. Add @brown rice{3/4%cups} and
cook until tender, ~{35-45%minutes}. Drain, then return to pot and keep
covered.

Wash and dry all produce. Cut @eggplant{1} into ½-inch cubes. Slice
@yellow squash{1} crosswise into thin rounds. Trim, then thinly slice
@scallions{2}, keeping greens and whites separate. Thinly slice
@garlic{2%cloves}. Peel @ginger{1%tbsp}, then mince until you have 1 TBSP.
Cut @lime{1} into wedges.

Heat a large drizzle of @vegetable oil{} in a large pan over medium heat. Add
eggplant and squash. Cook, tossing, until tender and lightly browned,
~{7-8%minutes}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Remove from pan and set aside.

Heat a drizzle of vegetable oil in same pan over medium heat. Add scallion
whites, ginger, and garlic. Cook, tossing, until fragrant, about ~{1%minute}.
Add @ground pork{8%oz} and break up meat into pieces with a #spatula{} or
#wooden spoon{}. Cook until lightly browned and no longer pink,
~{4-5%minutes}. Season with salt and pepper.

Return eggplant and squash to pan. Stir in @soy sauce{2%tbsp} and
@sesame oil{1%tbsp}. Cook, tossing, until veggies are warmed through.

Divide rice between plates, then top with stir-fry. Garnish with scallion
greens. Serve with lime wedges on the side for squeezing over.